#: mop/data/projects/tarsr.py:64
msgid "tracing_description_1"
msgstr ""
"Our project aims to shed light on the Southern Balkan Peninsula during "
"the First World War (1914-1918) and in particular on the regions of "
"Prilep-Bitola and Mariovo behind the so-called <span class=\"fst-"
"italic\">Salonica Front</span> or <span class=\"fst-italic\">Macedonian "
"Front</span> in today’s Republic of N. Macedonia."

#: mop/data/projects/tarsr.py:65
msgid "tracing_description_2"
msgstr ""
"Closely connected to wars and armed conflicts is their devastating impact"
" on the World’s Cultural Heritage. In our project we would like to follow"
" up on the question of Cultural Heritage and research on it during the "
"First World War."

#: mop/data/projects/tarsr.py:66
msgid "tracing_description_3"
msgstr ""
"Various historical and ecclesiastical monuments were severely afflicted "
"by the destruction along the <span class=\"fst-italic\">Salonica "
"Front</span>. Examples are the church of Saint Christopher in the village"
" of Krstoar and the Church of St. Nicholas in the village of Gradešnica. "
"Thorough scholarly research is still needed to evaluate the relevant "
"sources, especially the pictorial ones, on the particular monuments in "
"the region from Byzantine and Post-Byzantine times in order to receive a "
"comprehensive picture of the respective Cultural Heritage."

#: mop/data/projects/tarsr.py:67
msgid "tracing_description_4"
msgstr "Three research questions will be pursued:"

#: mop/data/projects/tarsr.py:68
msgid "tracing_description_5"
msgstr ""
"<ul>\n"
"<li>Where was the Cultural Heritage behind the <span class=\"fst-"
"italic\">Salonica Front</span> in the regions of Prilep-Bitola and "
"Mariovo affected by the fighting and how did the Central Powers document "
"the damage?</li>\n"
"<li>Where did archaeological excavations by the Central Powers take place"
" in the regions of Prilep-Bitola and Mariovo and who were the scholars "
"involved?</li>\n"
"<li>What kind of military infrastructure of the Central Powers can still "
"be traced <span class=\"fst-italic\">in situ</span> in the regions of "
"Prilep-Bitola and Mariovo (i.e. trenches, bunkers, roads, bridges, "
"tunnels, railways, ropeways, cemeteries)?</li>\n"
"</ul>"

#: mop/data/projects/tarsr.py:69
msgid "tracing_description_6"
msgstr ""
"The project and its novel approaches and methods in Historical Geography "
"have been introduced by Mihailo Popović to the interested public in the "
"digital version of the Austrian daily newspaper “Der Standard”. The "
"online article can be accessed via: <a "
"href=\"https://www.derstandard.at/story/3000000234089/im-fadenkreuz-der-"
"kriegsfotografie\" "
"target=\"_blank\">https://www.derstandard.at/story/3000000234089/im-"
"fadenkreuz-der-kriegsfotografie</a>"

